<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idf709807e-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idf709807f-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2017—Subsec. (b). <ref href="/us/pl/115/91">Pub. L. 115–91</ref> amended subsec. (b) generally. Prior to amendment, subsec. (b) read as follows:</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">“(b) <inline class="small-caps">Venue</inline>.—A person violating section 70503 or 70508 of this title shall be tried in the district court of the United States for—</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I22" class="indent1">“(1) the district at which the person enters the United States; or</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I22" class="indent1">“(2) the District of Columbia.”</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2008—Subsec. (b). <ref href="/us/pl/110/407">Pub. L. 110–407</ref> inserted “or 70508” after “70503” in introductory provisions.</p>
</note>
